8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 182, L.D. 396, “An Act to Provide for a
10 Later Starting Time for High Schools”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'Resolve, Directing the Department of Education to Develop a Grant Program to
13 Encourage School Start Time Coordination'
14 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the title and inserting the following:
15 'Sec. 1. School Start Time Fund established. Resolved: That the School Start
16 Time Fund is established within the Department of Education for the purposes of
17 administering the program under section 2.
18 Sec. 2. Grant program. Resolved: That the Department of Education shall
19 establish a grant program to encourage school administrative units to collaborate on
20 changing school start times to allow secondary schools to have a later start time than
21 elementary schools. The department shall award grants from the School Start Time Fund
22 established in section 1. Funds must be used by a school administrative unit to develop
23 plans to coordinate staggered school start times among the unit's schools or in partnership
24 with neighboring school administrative units.
25 Sec. 3. Appropriations and allocations. Resolved: That the following
26 appropriations and allocations are made.
27 EDUCATION, DEPARTMENT OF
28 Innovative Teaching and Learning Z394
29 Initiative: Provides one-time funds for a contracted position to administer the school start
30 time grant program.
31 GENERAL FUND 2025-26 2026-27
32 All Other $100,000 $0
