19 SUMMARY
2200 This amendment replaces the bill with a resolve. The amendment establishes the
2211 School Start Time Fund within the Department of Education and directs the department to
2222 develop a grant program to award funds to school administrative units to coordinate
2233 changing school start times to allow secondary schools to have a later start time than
2244 elementary schools. Funds awarded through the grant program must be used by a school
2255 administrative unit to develop plans to coordinate staggered start times either among the
2266 unit's own schools or in partnership with neighboring school administrative units.
